re happy to coach younger children in maths before they headed of to university for their maths degrees for a very nominal fee. Their enthusiasm for the subject they love rubbing of on some reluctant youngsters. As my daughter says 'maths is fun because it's solving the puzzle'...Too many children are desperately unhappy at school and would do better out of it. Too many children think they are hopeless at something like maths because they haven't had the right teacher and are trying to learn in a classroom where anarchy reigns. &#10;School should educate, but sometimes it doesn't."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="890" language="en" documentId="802" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="har23" date="07 January 2011 1:53pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/9052894" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="6" thumbsDown="0" origId="802" notes="" title="Why I home school my children"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="841"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="842" end="890"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>